\f0\fs28 \cf0 In \'93The Basics\'94, we covered how {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://807F5B29-A760-492A-8C3B-427499C811EF"}}{\fldrslt coloured labels}} can be assigned to documents, and how they can be used for anything. There\'92s a cool way of viewing labels that we didn\'92t cover when looking at the basics, though: labels can be displayed in threads on the corkboard view. The easiest way to understand how this works is to see it in action:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://6DA3324E-530B-4B9B-93EC-763F87C25D00"}}{\fldrslt Split the editor}} if necessary.\
{\listtext	2.	}In the other editor, load the \'93Writing and Editing\'94 folder under \'93Going Further\'94.\
{\listtext	3.	}Switch to corkboard mode. You should see several cards on the board.\
{\listtext	4.	}From the main menu, select 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::0>
\f2\b View > Corkboard Options > Show Label Colors Along Edges
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::0>
\f0\fs28  so that you can see the label colours in the corkboard. (You don\'92t need to do this, but it\'92s useful for this demonstration.)\
{\listtext	5.	}Either select 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::0>
\f2\b View > Corkboard Options > Arrange by Label
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::0>
\f0\fs28  from the main menu, or click on this button in the footer bar:\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural\qc\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 {\*\shppict{\pict {\*\nisusfilename ArrangeByLabelButton}\picw93\pich34\picwgoal1860\pichgoal680\pngblip }}
\f0\fs28 \
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 See what happens? Coloured lines appear stretching the width of the corkboard, each representing a label. Each card is placed on the line that corresponds to the label associated with its document, in the same order as it appears in the binder.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Drag cards from left to right to change their positions in the binder.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Drag cards up and down to change their labels.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Switch between horizontal and vertical lines using the button in the footer bar.\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 If you\'92re writing a novel and use labels to keep track of the point-of-view character or subplot for each document, this is a great way of viewing all the threads in a group. (And combined with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivlnk://BD51CEFB-04E0-4CC3-9DCA-728DE9DA40A9"}}{\fldrslt viewing multiple groups}}, you could even view threads for the entire manuscript.)}